non-oil exports and a larger than expected decline in imports.
Indonesia was again congratulated for reducing poverty from 60 per cent of
the population in 1970 to 15 per cent.
But it was warned it faced growing competition, particularly from
newly-liberalised economies among its Asian neighbours, in expanding and
diversifying exports and attracting foreign investment.
The donors' group took note of the government's recent de-regulation in
cutting tariffs and non-tariffs, and agreed Indonesia needed to reduce
further its bureaucratic obstacles.
</TEXT>
